Third best Star Wars movie ever for me!

My top 3 are:
1. Revenge of the Sith
2. The Empire Strikes Back
3. The Rise of Skywalker

I honestly felt like from the moment it started until it ended I loved every second of it, for me it was such an interesting story (I was 100% hooked in). I haven't felt this way about anything Star Wars since Revenge of the Sith, for me it's all about the story and this story was very was engaging. It was subject matter that actually mattered to me as a viewer and Star Wars fan, It literally exceeded every possible expectation I could have had for it. I honestly can't even fathom that anyone couldn't love it. I felt like JJ pulled the whole thing together and saved the whole final trilogy from being an epic disaster (after the Last Jedi, which I like but is my least favorite Star Wars film out of all of them), I only hoped for decent (I got near perfection). 
I felt like this was the ultimate Thank you üôè to us Star Wars fans that have been there since the beginning, almost a love letter to us to say "Thank you and we appreciate you"!

I can't fathom any negativity toward it in ANY way.
Things that would have made this 5 stars for me: Anakin showing up in ghost form & Rey being a clone of some sort. Overall good stuff.
Overall great. The cameos was horrible tho. Did anyone else catch the small item at the ending? Think there will be another one. Or at least to Disney +?

Good rescue after the terrible Last Jedi. There's a lot going on but JJ did the best he could do with what he was given. I need to see it again but my first reaction is that it was a very satisfying conclusion.

A movie full of nostalgia, love, action, surprises and unexpected twists. Thank you Star Wars for what you made me feel yesterday. Thank you for giving me and my family a unique moment. The force will be with us always. (1977-2019)
good way the end the series of movies

Interesting how this is essentially flipped from when TLJ came out.  Critics loved it, but we thought it was dog excrement.  Critics not so hot on Rise of Skywalker, but we liked it.  So go with what audience thinks for the most part.

If you're a child, you'll probably enjoy it since it doesn't take much to impress kids.
If you're an adult with low expectations ,who's easily amused, you'll probably enjoy it too.

If you have seen ANY Star Wars movie made before 2005, you will see this for the garbage that it is and leave disappointed.

I wasn't sure what to expect, but I loved the movie. Thought it rounded off the saga brilliantly, and threw in a few curve balls as well. Won't please everyone, but then no film ever could. Glad I saw it before seeing the critics reviews took the shine off the experience for me.
